igh as 10^{25} cm^-2. This makes ESO 138-G1 a very interesting, heavy\nCompton-thick AGN candidate for the next X-ray missions with spectroscopic and\nimaging capabilities above 10 keV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Aug 2011 10:00:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-30"}
